Todd Fischer (born August 23, 1969) is an American professional golfer. Fischer was born in Columbus, Ohio. He played college golf at the University of San Francisco, where he won two events.[1] Fischer played on the Nationwide Tour and PGA Tour from 2001 to 2011. On the Nationwide Tour, 200102 and 200711, his best finish was a win at the 2002 Fort Smith Classic. On the PGA Tour, 200306, He had four third place finishes: 3rd at the 2003 Greater Hartford Open, T-3 at the 2004 B.C. Open, T-3 at the 2004 Valero Texas Open, and 3rd at 2005 Reno-Tahoe Open.[2] 
